latestIgtvVideos.title: backbend flow ✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The injury on my back is recovering now and the doctor has told me to move at a slow pace.🥰

I clearly remember that with the lack of time I was pushing my body to do stretches that need a lot of warming up! 
Because I had to take sessions or gymnast classes, or studies. 
I was being hard on myself :/

But This recovering phase has taught me to handle my body with patience and that I should prioritize myself over anything!! 

So here's a backbend flow I practiced today where I am not being hard on my back. letting it recover with time. 

This is a whole-body stretch I prefer doing before doing any advanced stretches. Any level can practice this backbend flow with their creative variations ✨

latestPosts.caption:
✨ DAY 2 - Movement to Release Stuck Energy ✨
(From the 21 Days Basic Series before our big YouTube Challenge!)

Remember how we used to move freely as kids?
Shake, stretch, jump, tap — no rules, just joy.
Today’s practice is not a workout.
It’s a release.
It’s a way to clear the stale energy stored in your body.

When you don’t move, that stuck energy turns into:
😤 Anger
😟 Anxiety
🥱 Fatigue
🍩 Even fat storage

Let’s not carry the weight of yesterday into today.

🌀 Practices included today:
1) Shaking – releases stuck tension & stress
2) Jumping – ignites your energy
3)Clapping – activates blood flow, opens energy blocks
4)Full body tapping – boosts circulation, awakens nerves
5)Finger pulling – releases emotional pressure linked to each element
6)Humming – calms the nervous system
7)Active exhalation – powerful detox through breath
8) Dancing/ jumping– builds deep self-connection

🌞 This 21-day series is to help you build a strong yogic base
before we begin our 21st June YouTube Challenge!
Let’s walk into it feeling lighter, clearer & deeply connected.

#MovementHeals #BasicSeries #KhushiBajwaYoga #21DayYogaChallenge #MorningRoutine #StuckEnergyRelease #YogaOffTheMat #HealingMovement

✨ Let me re-introduce myself… ✨
For all the beautiful souls who’ve just joined this space — welcome! 🤍

I’m Khushi Bajwa, your Yoga teacher, a practitioner of the yogic path for over 6 years now. This journey has been nothing short of sacred for me — a moving meditation, a daily prayer, a deep remembering. 🌿

🧘‍♀️ I am an Ashtanga practitioner, certified to teach the Primary Series, and I hold a Diploma in Yoga from Morarji Desai Institute.
📜 I’m also YCB Level 2 certified (Yoga Certification Board).
🌺 Alongside Yoga, I practice and offer Reiki healing, embracing the subtle layers of energy and transformation.
🎓 Currently, I’m pursuing my MSc in Yoga from S-VYASA — diving deeper into the philosophy, science, and therapy of this ancient wisdom.

One of the most beautiful realisations on this path has been understanding the true meaning of Yoga — union.
The moment I felt that deeply, it started showing up off the mat as well.
✨ When I sip tea and watch the trees — that’s Yoga.
✨ When I move my body with awareness — that’s Yoga.
✨ When I work mindfully on my laptop — that’s also Yoga.
Yoga is the union of breath and body, mind and present moment, intention and action.

And if you’re wondering what I’m like —
I’m super disciplined with my practice, and honestly, I love it. I love my healthy routine, my clean eating, and living in alignment.
You can give me fruits all day — I’ll never say no. 🍇🍊
Even karela juice? If you say it’s healthy, I’ll drink it — no drama! 😄
I’m not controlled by my taste buds — I genuinely enjoy what’s good for the body.

This practice has gifted me discipline, stillness, and the power to find peace even in the middle of chaos.

I’m truly grateful you’re here. Let’s grow together — inside and out. 🌱

Now, tell me about you?
Are you starting your journey, looking for motivation, or already a teacher? I’d love to know! 💬

#yogajourney

Today, I’m sharing my slow and gentle Sunday morning routine — my Me Time, where I connect with myself and set a calm, positive tone for the day. 

Remember, yoga isn’t just about poses; it’s about slowing down, being present, and taking care of your mind and body. Your Me Time is your yoga. 💛

My all-time fav Hip Mobility Stretches!
These are the ones I always come back to when my hips feel tight or heavy
💕Save & try them out today

Here’s how to practice:
	1.	Do each movement 10 times
	2.	If it’s one-sided, repeat on the other leg too
	3.	Inhale as you move away from the ground
	4.	Exhale as you go towards the ground

Your hips store emotions – open them up & release what’s stuck
Which one was your fav? Tell me in the comments!💕
